post_text:
Some responses from concert reflections in 1st-3rd grades:

I felt surprised that the classmates would be silly but they weren't. (C.C.)
I felt happy because I did not have any fears because we do this all the time. (J.J.)
I felt good because I knew the songs well and I wasn't nervous. (G.F.)
I felt happy because I love concerts and it was really fun.
I felt happy because it was my first recorder concert. (K.B.)
I felt happy because I liked it when everyone was blowing bubbles. (K.R.)
I felt impressed because I did my best singing. (A.R.)
I felt happy and nervous because I like concerts. (S.B.)
I felt happy and excited because it is fun to perform. (L.C.)
I felt excited (happy) because we sang clearly (R.S.)

Great job, everyone!
